:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/I030182/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>Working with the Scottish Council for Voluntary Organisations (SCVO), this research aims to provide insight into issues related to the use of micro-simulation to model future health and social care provision for older people in Scotland and the third sector's role in providing that care. Patterns of service and modes of delivery are expected to change in response to drivers including:&lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>increasing demand; spiralling costs of provision&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>reductions in public spending&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>policy initiatives to promote self-directed support and shift the balance of care.&lt;/li>

&lt;/ul>

&lt;p>Modelling can facilitate evaluation and interrogation of the third sector contribution, estimation of optimal mixes of services, and identification of service growth and capacity issues, but requires adequately robust inputs.&lt;br />&lt;br />The study reviews literature on service output evaluation and uses case studies to assess the ability of different approaches to illuminate services? wider contributions to care, including substitution effects. It identifies organisation and sector level information requirements for modelling, reviews existing datasets and data capture mechanisms, surveys third sector providers, identifies gaps and makes recommendations. Findings will be of particular value to local and national policy makers and planners seeking to better understand the contribution of the third sector to health and social care provision.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2012-03-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2011-05-23</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>22622</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Meeting with Evaluation Services Scotland</gtr:description><gtr:form>A formal working group, expert panel or dialogue</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>Regional</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>24DCE1E4-71E9-408A-862E-6484768F38C7</gtr:id><gtr:impact>Meeting requested by Diane Kennedy of Evaluation Servies Scotland to discuss Fellowship findings, 'micro-mapping' techniques, and issues related to preventative service use. Discussions to inform 'A Stitch in Time?', a partnership demonstration project facilitated by Evaluation Support Scotland and supported by the Scottish Government Third Sector Division and the Joint Improveme